Three poachers were on Wednesday gunned down by Kenya Wildlife Service officers at Mt. Elgon National Park in Trans Nzoia County. KWS Spokesperson and Head Corporate Communications Paul Gathitu said in a statement that the KWS officers who were on routine patrol inside the park encountered five poachers, two of whom were armed. Read:Â Poachers kill three rhinos at Meru National Park "An exchange of fire between the KWS team and the poachers resulted in three of the poachers being shot dead. The two poachers who were armed managed to escape with injuries," he said. The KWS team recovered various paraphernalia commonly used by poachers from the scene of the incident. Click here for the latest political news